cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.DS

This paper is about hardware acceleration of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) with weight sharing. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.AR (Hardware Architecture for Neural Networks), as the paper focuses on designing a hardware accelerator for CNNs. The paper also deals with image processing, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for reducing power consumption and gate count, which could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed method on FPGAs, which could be relevant to cs.DS (Digital Systems).
